### Requirement 10 — Cloudinary Config: String | Undefined Type Fix

**User Story:** As a developer deploying image uploads, I want the Cloudinary configuration to compile without TypeScript errors, so that product image upload functionality is available when Cloudinary credentials are set.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. THE CloudinaryConfig SHALL cast the Cloudinary credential environment variables to `string` only when they are defined, or SHALL use a type assertion pattern (e.g., `as any`) that satisfies the Cloudinary SDK type signature without relying on `string | undefined`.
2. THE CloudinaryConfig SHALL NOT pass `undefined` directly to `cloud_name`, `api_key`, or `api_secret` fields of `cloudinary.config()` when TypeScript strict mode is active.
3. THE TypeScript compiler SHALL produce zero type errors in `cloudinary.ts` after this fix.

