### Requirement 18 — Frontend AdminUsers: updateUserRole and deleteUser Endpoints

**User Story:** As an administrator, I want the Promote/Demote and Delete buttons on the Admin Users page to call working backend endpoints, so that user management actions take effect.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. THE ApiClient `updateUserRole` method SHALL call `PUT /admin/users/:id/role` with body `{ role: string }`, matching the new endpoint defined in Requirement 12.
2. THE ApiClient `deleteUser` method SHALL call `DELETE /admin/users/:id`, matching the new endpoint defined in Requirement 13.
3. WHEN an admin clicks Promote or Demote on AdminUsers.tsx, THE Frontend SHALL call `apiClient.updateUserRole` and, upon a 200 response, shall refresh the user list.
4. WHEN an admin clicks Delete on AdminUsers.tsx, THE Frontend SHALL call `apiClient.deleteUser` and, upon a 200 response, shall refresh the user list.

